{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778123110,"nonce":"AUU/GpmSUZ5Lgvft12lBjzYBRqw=","title":"Phase 2 completion: split spec/artifact configs, wire feedbax figure-spec, document run-ID rename","message":"Phase 2 of the structure migration (\\`fd64bb4\\`, merged via \\`c27e61bf\\`) deferred 3 items. Finishing them now.\n\n## 1. Train scripts split spec from artifact paths\n\n\\`scripts/train_minimax.py\\` and \\`scripts/train_part2_5.py\\` currently write \\`config.json\\` to the bulk \\`--output-dir\\` (now \\`_artifacts/...\\`). Per the structure spec, configs are spec files and should go to \\`results/\u003cexp\u003e/runs/\u003crun\u003e/run.json\\` (using the canonical \\`run.json\\` name).\n\n**Implement:** add \\`--spec-dir\\` CLI argument that defaults to the mirror of \\`--output-dir\\` under \\`results/\\`, OR auto-derive from \\`paths.run_artifact_dir\\` ↔ \\`paths.run_spec_dir\\`. Train scripts then write the run config to the spec dir as \\`run.json\\` (and weights/optimizer/logs to the artifact dir).\n\n## 2. Wire feedbax `save_figure_with_spec` into eval scripts\n\n\\`scripts/eval_part2_5_figures.py\\` (and other eval scripts) write \\`.html\\` figures next to model files. Now that feedbax \\`save_figure_with_spec\\` (helper merged via feedbax \\`1b5daf70\\`) is available, eval scripts should use it: emit \\`spec.json\\` to \\`paths.figure_spec_dir(exp, fig)\\` (committable) and the rendered figure to \\`paths.figure_artifact_dir(exp, fig)\\` (gitignored, threshold-gated).\n\n**Implement:** import \\`from feedbax.plot.io import save_figure_with_spec\\`. Replace direct \\`fig.write_html(...)\\` calls with \\`save_figure_with_spec(fig, spec, dst_dir)\\`. Build spec dict per the helper's contract (inputs + transform + plot_kwargs + versions).\n\n## 3. Old run-ID directory naming\n\nPhase 2 renamed script defaults to \\`\u003cgroup\u003e__\u003cvariant\u003e\\` double-underscore (